observations.recommendation:
We recommended the MGSO to:

Submit RPCI totalling ₱58.064 million as of December 31, 2023, duly supported with Inventory Count Forms, Certified copies of Stock cards, if there are any;

Maintain and update Stock Cards for all inventory items and to record the receipts and issuance thereof;

Promptly prepare and submit monthly SSMI to the MA duly supported with approved RIS and FCR for FOL products so that issuances thereof are timely recorded and accounted for in the books of accounts; and

Conduct reconciliation of FOL products with supplier records to come up with an updated and correct inventory balance of FOL products as at year-end and submit the same to the MA for adjustment in the accounting records.

We recommended the Municipal Engineer to:

Notify in writing the Contractor to enforce the warranty and rectify the defects/damage of the Expansion of Poblacion Potable Water System project to make it operational and beneficial;

Defer the release of Retention Money and other related claims of the contractor to compel the latter to rectify the defects;

Consider blacklisting the contractor in participating future projects of the LGU to avoid recurrence of similar issue; and

Conduct further detailed engineering studies to correct project defects and improve the efficacy and ensure non-recurrence of sustained damage.

Municipal Mayor along with all the concerned officials and employees strictly follow the provisions of DILG-DBM Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2017-1 in planning the PPAs funded by 20% DF and their implementation. See to it that those development projects identified in the AIP were fully implemented for the benefit of the constituents;

Executive Committee of the LDC identify and prioritize the development projects that could be implemented during the year by taking into consideration the technical manpower of the Municipality.  Consider changing the PPAs in the AIPs which cannot be implemented during the year to other viable developmental projects, subject to the approval of the SB; and

Consider the creation of a unit under the Office of the Municipal Mayor to purposely monitor the various identified PPAs to be implemented during the year funded by the 20% DF.

We recommended that the management:

Require the Municipal Engineer to:

Call the attention of the Contractor to fast tract completion of the project;

Submit copies of the approved Work Suspension Orders, duly supported with PAGASA weather report;

Compute the Negative Slippage to determine appropriate action to be taken against the contractor; and

Direct the MA to impose liquidated damages prior to payment.

The Municipal Mayor and OIC-Municipal Engineer shall institute legal actions against the contractor for failure to undertake and/or complete the project within the periods specified in the contract, including but not limited to:

Termination of the Contract;

Require the contractor to return the mobilization fee (for Rehab. And Concreting of Moyo-Pase FMR) collected from the LGU and DAR-ARCP II;

Blacklist the contractor and disqualify it from participating future procurement projects of the LGU; and

Return to DAR-ARCP II any unused project funds
